cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper deals with software systems and their adaptation to changes and uncertainties. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a machine learning approach to predict the performance of the system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with self-adaptation of systems and their performance under different configurations. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper evaluates the approach on stream processing applications and a NoSQL database system. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with configuration capabilities of software systems.
